<font color="#FF0000">IT WAS WAR!!!</font><br>
<tt>Tue Sep 16 13:10:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
JOHN, GOODBYE,<br><br>
Get off your High Horse. When I first visited here in June I read all of the trash, filthy language, and condemnation against those that fought in Vietnam posted by certain individuals who condemned the war and used this site for their very own self promotion, glorification and gratification at the expense of the occasional Vietnam vet that would wonder in and out. <br>
This site was X-rated by any standards and I would not allow my daughters to read the words spatz posted against those that disagreed with him. The response he got is evident by the very descriptive words vets responding to him used. <br>
Those vets never came back. <br>
GO back and e-mail all those vets and you'll understand why they stopped posting. It was no dialog, it was a lecture by those that condemned the war, no matter what.<br>
Then I saw how  you and others tried to play the Geneva convention role, lets hold hands and why can't we all get along.  What a song that has been.<br><br>
Going back I realized what I have posted via languages or calling the enemy communist gooks, has been debated, argued and trashed around months before I got here. Those vets never returned. <br>
The language and what conversations we have recently shared has been that of individuals that saw the war differently, who paid a heavy price for their involvement in actual COMBAT. <br>
A much different type of action then what others who had posted here before had stated or spoke about. Finally individuals that had insight into both sides of the Vietnam issue and who were and are not afraid to state what they believe and that went contrary to what was acceptable here by a bunch of draft dodgers and individuals that saw more action during one 15 minute evening news special program about the war then in all the time they served in Vietnam. Individuals that saw very little action and then condemned all those that reflected upon what they did then and what they are doing today. <br>
Going back its easy to see that each and every time anyone stated they supported the Vietnam vet for their actions in Vietnam, they were abused, insulted and crapped all over and it made no difference if the individual posting was a vet, Asian, a student, an educator or anyone seeking info about the war. <br>
All they got was one sided matter of fact statements and if you argue with us, we know we're right and go someplace else. <br><br>
Any educator worth their salt that is tired of a one sided argument about the Vietnam war can easily gleam the rich and valuable insights I and others have shared and posted recently about what it meant to many Americans who were fighting men that felt pride and honor for their accomplishment and involvement in the war in South East Asia. Who did the actual shooting and who served with honor and are not Winter Soldiers crying about what was wrong with the war and what they did.<br>
 Yes, Children, women and innocent people died but here it's still the Vietnam Vet being blamed for that. <br>
 IT WAS AWAR!!!!!!. <br><br>
Art said it best, <br>
&quot;This society has to learn that it cannot judge war conduct as it does civilian conduct.&quot; <br><br>
What do you do when a communist gook in a tan colored uniform shoots at you from in front of a hooch and you return fire. He keeps firing and you fire a rocket at him. The rocket misses its mark and hits the hooch, behind him. <br>
That is what has been emphasized here. The destruction to the hooch or the people inside the hooch. What had not been considered before was why that gook choose to fire at us from in front of the hooch in the first place. We're condemned for returning fire and killing the individuals inside the hooch. The problem is we felt guilt for having killed innocent women and children who got in the line of fire, the enemy never did. They used it and you and others have used it here to justify your stand against the war.. <br>
The problem you and others have is that you have ran this show all one sided. All pointing fingers at how wrong the war was and making veterans feel guilty about their service to American or the Vietnamese people. <br><br>
It sounds like your playing somebody's else's tune for them, once again.<br><br>

<p><code>-- Posted-  (Cook Barela, USMC Vietnam 67-68) </code><p>


